    intro: 'Franz Schubert lived just 31 years, yet he produced one of the most astonishing bodies of work in musical history — over 600 songs, nine symphonies, chamber music of unparalleled beauty, and piano works of deep emotional power. He bridged the Classical elegance of Mozart and Beethoven with the emotional intensity of Romanticism.',
