    career: 'Unlike most composers of his era, Schubert never held a major musical post. He lived among a devoted circle of friends — the famous "Schubertiades" — informal gatherings where his songs and chamber works were performed. Though he struggled financially and never achieved wide fame in his lifetime, he composed at a breathtaking pace, transforming the art song into a vehicle of profound emotional expression.',
    legacy: 'Schubert died at 31, buried near Beethoven at his own request. Much of his music was unpublished during his lifetime — the "Great" C major Symphony was not performed until Schumann discovered the manuscript a decade after Schubert\'s death. Today he is recognized as the father of the art song and one of the most naturally gifted melodists in the history of Western music.',
