    intro: 'Igor Stravinsky is widely regarded as one of the most important and influential composers of the 20th century. His work spans an extraordinary range of styles — from the explosive primitivism of The Rite of Spring to elegant neoclassicism to late-career serialism — each phase reshaping the musical landscape.',
    earlyLife: 'Born in Oranienbaum, near St. Petersburg, Russia, in 1882, Stravinsky was the son of a leading bass singer at the Mariinsky Theatre. Though his parents steered him toward law, he studied privately with Nikolai Rimsky-Korsakov, who became his most important mentor and opened the door to the world of orchestration.',
