    intro: 'Edvard Grieg is Norway\'s most celebrated composer and one of the leading figures of the Romantic nationalist movement in music. His works draw deeply on Norwegian folk melodies and dance rhythms, transforming them into art music of extraordinary beauty, harmonic inventiveness, and emotional directness.',
    earlyLife: 'Born in Bergen, Norway, in 1843, Grieg showed musical talent from an early age. His mother, a pianist and music teacher, gave him his first piano lessons at age six. At 15, on the advice of the famous violinist Ole Bull, he was sent to the Leipzig Conservatory in Germany, where he immersed himself in the Romantic tradition of Schumann and Mendelssohn.',
