    intro: 'Sir Elton Hercules John is one of the most commercially successful and enduring artists in music history. His four-decade partnership with lyricist Bernie Taupin produced some of the most beloved songs in popular music. With over 300 million records sold, flamboyant stage costumes, and extraordinary piano skills, he became one of the defining figures of 1970s rock.',
    earlyLife: 'Born Reginald Kenneth Dwight on March 25, 1947, in Pinner, Middlesex, England. He began playing piano at age three and won a scholarship to the Royal Academy of Music at 11. In 1967, he answered a newspaper ad from Liberty Records and was paired with lyricist Bernie Taupin — the beginning of one of songwriting\'s greatest partnerships.',
