    intro: 'Marvin Pentz Gay Jr. (he added the "e" to his surname) was one of the most important and influential artists in American popular music. He began as a smooth Motown hit-maker and evolved into a visionary artist whose What\'s Going On is widely regarded as one of the greatest albums ever made — a soulful meditation on war, poverty, ecology, and spirituality.',
    earlyLife: 'Born on April 2, 1939, in Washington, D.C. His father was a church minister who frequently beat him. Marvin found solace in music, singing in his father\'s church choir and teaching himself piano, drums, and guitar. After a stint in the Air Force, he moved to Detroit and auditioned for Berry Gordy\'s Motown Records.',
