    intro: 'James Joseph Brown was the most important rhythmic innovator in 20th-century popular music. He transformed soul music into funk by shifting the emphasis from melody and harmony to rhythm and groove, creating the musical foundation for disco, hip-hop, and electronic dance music. He is the most sampled artist in music history.',
