    career: 'After leaving Ike, Tina spent years performing in small venues. Her comeback began with a cover of Al Green\'s "Let\'s Stay Together" (1983). Private Dancer (1984) sold 20 million copies and won four Grammy Awards. "What\'s Love Got to Do with It" became her signature hit. She became the first solo female artist to fill stadiums, and her farewell tours broke attendance records worldwide.',
    legacy: 'Tina Turner sold over 200 million records and won 12 Grammy Awards including a Lifetime Achievement Award. She was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame twice — with Ike Turner in 1991 and as a solo artist in 2021. Her story of survival and triumph inspired millions. She died on May 24, 2023, at age 83 in Switzerland.',
